What exactly is a hybrid mattress? A hybrid mattress combines the best of both worlds, integrating the coil springs found in traditional innerspring mattresses with the plush comfort of memory foam. This dual construction provides an optimal balance of support, comfort & durability. What are the main benefits of choosing a hybrid mattress over other types? The hybrid mattress offers: Adaptive Support; Pressure Relief; Durability; Temperature Regulation; Reduced Motion Transfer Is a hybrid mattress suitable for side, back, or stomach sleepers? Yes! The beauty of a hybrid mattress is its versatility. The spring coils offer the required support for back and stomach sleepers, while the memory foam provide the cushioning that side sleepers need for their shoulders and hips. How do I know if a hybrid mattress is the right choice for me? The suitability of a hybrid mattress depends on your individual preferences and needs. If you enjoy the combination of support and comfort, desire reduced motion transfer, or tend to sleep hot, a hybrid mattress could be an excellent choice. Do hybrid mattresses require any special maintenance or care? While hybrid mattresses are relatively low-maintenance, there are some essential care tips to ensure their longevity. Rotate your mattress every 3-6 months to promote even wear. and use a mattress protector can help prevent stains and damage.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My Son LOVES This
reviews.reviewText: I caught this on sale for my oldest son’s impending launch, with the expectation we’d store it in his closet until he was ready to move (a few months from now- he’s in his last semester of his college program). He has a smaller closet, and the way it’s packaged makes it totally feasible to stand in a back corner until you’re ready to open it. As it turns out, he was excited and ready to open it now. Oof.Fast forward 10 days, after I’ve ordered the up-sized bed frame and mattress protector (I’d already bought the sheets, pillows, and comforter set) and arranged to borrow the neighbor’s guest bedroom so the mattress had a flat place to lay undisturbed for three days, and now he’s lodged a complaint that this new bed is too comfortable and he’s struggling to make himself get out of it for his 9 a.m. class.Our experience was kind of an obstacle course, but here’s what you need to know:• The package is heavier than it looks. Proceed accordingly.• Don’t open the plastic vacuum wrap until you’ve got a flat surface this can lay on for a few days to fully re-inflate.• We didn’t notice any strong odors after opening.• It expands rapidly when you open the plastic. Like… RoadRunner cartoon rapidly. Proceed accordingly.• Standard full-size sheets and mattress protectors accommodate it just fine.• It’s more plush than we expected, but still has minimal motion transfer.• It really does stay cool. My kid sleeps hot and even after sleeping on it for 8 hours, he’s still comfortable when he wakes up.• We have it on a bed frame with closely-spaced metal slats and no box spring, and it’s still fully supportive. I’ll add a board to extend the life of the mattress, but it’s comfortable without either.• I had also planned to add a 3” mattress topper to this when I bought it, to further extend the life of the mattress. I’m still going to do that, but for comfort and cooling, it’s not necessary.• It’s too soft for me, but I have a long-standing angry hip flexor condition that demands a bed only slightly softer than a sheet of plywood.Overall, we are super impressed with this mattress; both at the sale price AND the regular price and we recommend it. It’s a fantastic value.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This is a quality product
reviews.reviewText: This Nap Queen mattress easily shaped itself in a couple of days, and there was no odor of any kind. The corners filled in nicely also. I highly recommend a foam mattress such as this one which has the specially designed heavy foam coils at the bottom. These make such a big difference in balance and support, and I am guessing the mattress will keep its shape much longer than those built out of layered sheets of foam.I have a tricky antique bed which has carved side and end boards, and it has been difficult to accommodate, as it is neither a queen nor full in size. The air mattress I was using died of old age; this Nap Queen full mattress tucked right into the padded and zippered mattress cover which had held the air units. Perfect, and much more comfortable!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Never fully expanded
reviews.reviewText: When this thing arrived it sprang open immediately, but even with giving it multiple days to expand it never reached the size of a regular full mattress. It also was much softer than I expected. Meaning, I can feel the individual springs move when I do on the bed. They're not hard or pokey, they are just the first resistance felt to me sagging deeper and deeper into the mattress. The top is nice and soft, a little too soft allowing you to feel the inards. But overall it's a decent mattress for the price. Not noisy, or lumpy, or uneven. A good starter mattress, and an overall good deal.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2023
reviews.reviewText: We were nervous at first when taking this out of the box and opening up the seal. It did immediately start to expand but the ends didn't. It was like there was no foam on the 11" of each end. We ended up taking it outside into the sunshine to help it expand, since it says heat helps. This did the trick. We let our 10 year old sleep on it after 24 hours and she absolutely loves it. Her old mattress was awful and she's only 60 pounds, but it does seem comfortable. It did have some stuff on it which I lint rolled off. I can't tell what it is, but can see how some people said bug legs. I don't think it's that. Also, a few of the threads that give it the quilted top were loose. One corner didn't expand to 100% yet, so I'll report back on that and how it holds up later. So far, happy with the purchase.*update : it's been a couple months and she loves this mattress. It's the most comfortable one in the house, nice and soft. I took long nap on it one day and wish I hadn't gotten myself a different $1200 mattress, this is better.
